President Trump welcomes Team USA to the White House to honor their achievements at the 2018 Winter Olympics and Paralympics in South Korea. He commends the athletes for their dedication, hard work, and perseverance. The President also expresses his hope for peace and unity on the Korean Peninsula and announces his upcoming meeting with North Korean leader Kim Jong-un to discuss denuclearization. He individually recognizes and congratulates several athletes on their accomplishments, including Redmond Gerard, Arielle Gold, Mark Goepper, John-Henry Krueger, the U.S. Women's Hockey Team, Vincent Zhou, and the gold medal-winning curling team. The President concludes by thanking all the athletes for representing the United States and presents them with flags signed by the entire delegation.